<paragraph id="F45436C1FFE2FFBAFD89FCEDA807FB6D" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,1193]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFE2FFBAFD89FCEDAC36FC4D" author="Parodi, L. R." box="[189,343,878,904]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" pagination="183 - 212" refId="ref10950" refString="Parodi, L. R. (1941) Revision de las gramineas sudamericanas del genero Hierochloe. Revista del Museo de La Plata (N. S.) 3 (14): 183 - 212." type="journal article" year="1941">Parodi (1941)</bibRefCitation>
revised some plant materials sent from the Swedish Museum of Natural History Herbarium, but no typification was carried out. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFE2FFBAFF5FFC10AE43FC68" author="De Paula, M. E." box="[619,802,914,941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" pagination="422 - 457" refId="ref10151" refString="De Paula, M. E. (1975) Las especies del genero Hierochloe (Gramineae) de Argentina y Chile. Darwiniana 19: 422 - 457." type="journal article" year="1975">De Paula (1975)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned a clastotype from the 
<collectingRegion id="362FF823FFE2FFBAF9ACFC10A84EFC69" box="[1176,1327,914,941]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
University Herbarium (BAA), which was probably the same specimen seen by Parodi [a 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFE2FFBAF93EFC34A905FC14" box="[1034,1124,951,977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">syntype</typeStatus>
, since no 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFE2FFBAF9EEFC35A85DFC15" box="[1242,1340,950,976]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">holotype</typeStatus>
had been declared (Art. 9.10, Ex. 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE2FFBAFCA9FC59ACB7FC31" box="[413,470,986,1012]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFE2FFBAFCEAFC59AFA7FC30" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[478,710,986,1013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" refId="ref11638" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. [Regnum Vegetabile 159] Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFE2FFBAFF0AFC58AF10FC31" box="[574,625,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
)]. 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFE2FFBAFFD5FC59A955FC30" author="Schouten, Y. &amp; Veldkamp, J. F." box="[737,1076,986,1013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" pagination="319 - 351" refId="ref11216" refString="Schouten, Y. &amp; Veldkamp, J. F. (1985) A revision of Anthoxanthum including Hierochloe (Gramineae) in Malesia and Thailand. Blumea 30 (2): 319 - 351." type="journal article" year="1985">Schouten &amp; Veldkamp (1985)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFE2FFBAF9E2FC59A859FC31" box="[1238,1336,986,1012]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">holotype</typeStatus>
is housed in the Stockholm Herbarium, but made no reference to any particular plant, whereas 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFE2FFBAF95BFC7DA99AFBDD" author="Sede, S." box="[1135,1275,1022,1048]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" refId="ref11254" refString="Sede, S. (2012) Anthoxanthum. In: Anton, A. M. &amp; Zuloaga, F. O. (Eds.) Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina. Vol. 3 (II). Monocotyledoneae. Poaceae: Pooideae. Graficamente Ediciones, Cordoba. Available from: www. floraargentina. edu. ar (accessed 25 May 2017)" type="book" year="2012">Sede (2012)</bibRefCitation>
referred to the specimen S-R-2929 stored in S as the 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFE2FFBAFF08FBA1AFC3FBF9" box="[572,674,1058,1084]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">holotype</typeStatus>
. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFE2FFBAFE2AFBA1A947FBF9" author="Villalobos, N. &amp; Finot, V. &amp; Ruiz, E. &amp; Penailillo, P. &amp; Collado, G." box="[798,1062,1058,1084]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" pagination="93 - 136" refId="ref11988" refString="Villalobos, N., Finot, V., Ruiz, E., Penailillo, P. &amp; Collado, G. (2019) Estudio morfometrico y taxonomico de las especies nativas chilenas del genero Anthoxanthum (Poaceae, Pooideae, Poeae, Anthoxanthinae). Darwiniana, Nueva Serie 7: 93 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.14522 / darwiniana. 2019.71.822" type="journal article" year="2019">
Villalobos 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFE2FFBAFEADFBA0AEB2FBF9" box="[921,979,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
designated another plant from the Hackel herbarium in Wien (W) as the 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFE2FFBAFF0BFBC5AFC0FBA5" box="[575,673,1094,1120]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">holotype</typeStatus>
(W1916-0018309). Following Article 9.12 and recommendation 9A (1&amp;2) in 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFE2FFBAFDC7FBE9AC82FB41" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[243,483,1130,1157]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" refId="ref11638" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. [Regnum Vegetabile 159] Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFE2FFBAFC60FBE8ACE7FB41" box="[340,390,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
, we believe that the specimen S-R-2929 must be considered as 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFE2FFBAF989FBE9A846FB41" box="[1213,1319,1130,1156]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">lectotype</typeStatus>
, designated (inadvertently, as 
<typeStatus id="2B508863FFE2FFBAFC64FB0DACD5FB6C" box="[336,436,1166,1193]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">holotype</typeStatus>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="907A4B30FFE2FFBAFCD1FB0DAE56FB6C" author="Schouten, Y. &amp; Veldkamp, J. F." box="[485,823,1166,1193]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" pagination="319 - 351" refId="ref11216" refString="Schouten, Y. &amp; Veldkamp, J. F. (1985) A revision of Anthoxanthum including Hierochloe (Gramineae) in Malesia and Thailand. Blumea 30 (2): 319 - 351." type="journal article" year="1985">Schouten &amp; Veldkamp (1985)</bibRefCitation>
. The specimen in W is, therefore, an isolectotype.
</paragraph>
